def is_prime(n):  # check if n is prime number or not. return True or False.  O(sqrt(n)) method.  can be improved to O(log2n) method.  see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Primality_test#Pseudocode for more information.  
    if n == 2: return True # 2 is the only even prime number.  
    elif n % 2 == 0: return False # all other even numbers are not primes (exclude 2).  
    else: # odd numbers  
        i = 3 # start with 3 and go up to square root of n by 2 steps  
        while i*i <= n:   # if i > sqrt(n), then loop will exit because i*i = n or greater than sqrt(n)  
            if n % i == 0: return False # found a factor, so not prime  
            else: i += 2 # next odd number (step by 2)  
    return True
